Description: C3 has built a Security Orchestration SaaS Platform through the automation of analyst investigative workflows to streamline threat response.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Atlanta Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: C3 Orchestration is a subscription based SaaS with on-site lite gateway appliances that feed data into our cloud based orchestration engine. These gateways are deployed wherever necessary in order to obtain as much visibility as possible at every location with the least amount of effort to manage and deploy. Our orchestration engine is able to recognize data from any source and automatically structure it to be accurate and actionable. Rich data is the most important piece to catch and track down hacker activity. As we gather information in real-time, we take each security alert and our internal proprietary detection methods to kick off a full-scale investigation. These investigation playbooks use an automated process flow that can take top analyst hours or days to accurately correlate data across the entire environment. We are able to achieve this in seconds, providing a detailed case report with a step-by-step audit trail. Each case report generates a ticket into the preferred management platform and contains a suggested response for each threat and a supporting evidence package for additional analysis or legal review. The overall platform is designed for frictionless integration with the client’s central logging solution and to work seamlessly with the existing business processes using API generated response workflow tasks.
Industry Groups: Information Technology, Privacy and Security, Software
Founders: Christopher Corcoran, Matthew Pahl, Paul Smith

Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Talent Decisions is an easy to use SaaS candidate ranking and selection tool specifically built for recruiters and hiring managers. Designed to take a deeper look into job requirements, what candidates bring to the table and ultimately recruit the best possible individual for the role avoiding costly hiring mistakes. Based on cutting-edge academics from the London School of Economics and the founders background in recruiting, it puts structure around a decision which has never truly had one.  Kit holds an MSc in Decision Sciences from the LSE and had the privilege of studying under some of the pioneers in the field. He has been building and using ad-hoc excel based decision models on many of his search projects over the years. It allows him to deliver results faster, with greater insight and analysis than traditional recruiters. His vision was to take this complex and often messy Excel-based MCDA (multi-criteria decision analysis) model and create something web based and user-friendly.

Description: Chisholm Private Capital Partners focuses on early-stage and mezzanine investments and is a U.S.-based venture capital firm.
Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: Chisholm Private Capital Partners, LC is no longer investing. The firm is a venture capital firm specializing in investments in early stage companies. It also makes mezzanine investments. The firm does not invest in life style businesses and in non-United States based companies. It seeks to invest 75 percent of its capital in companies based in Oklahoma and 25 percent in companies based outside of Oklahoma. The firm typically invests between $1 million and $5 million in a company, normally in stages. In case of mezzanine investing, it invests between $2 million and $4 million. The firm invests in minority interest in the form of subordinate notes with warrants or preferred stock. It can also co-invest in larger mezzanine investments. The firm generally exits its investments within five years. It normally takes 20 percent to 50 percent of the amount invested. The firm seeks to be a lead investor and prefers to take a board seat in its portfolio companies. Chisholm Private Capital Partners, LC was founded in 1996 and is based in Oklahoma City, Oklahoma with additional offices in Tulsa, Oklahoma and Richardson, Texas.
